\section{Getting started}

%claude:
To get started you first need to get the source of the \plan
version described in this book. See \urlinstall.
%
Then you need to compile the \plan toolchain (compiler, assembler,
linker) and the profiling programs described in this book:
[[time]], [[prof]], [[tprof]], [[trace]], [[stats]], and [[iostats]].
%
To use [[prof]], you must link your target program with the
[[-p]] flag so that the linker inserts profiling instrumentation.
The [[tprof]] tool instead relies on kernel support
([[/proc/\emph{pid}/profile]]) and requires no special linking.

